width";i:981;s:6:"height";i:736;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/188236459410923331/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:59:{i:0;s:123:"A chair rail is a narrow strip of moulding that runs around the perimeter of a room usually about 36 inches off the ground.";i:1;s:104:"Use it to give a room a two-tone look or place it at the top of wainscoting for a more traditional feel.";i:2;s:95:"Full Size of Chairdining Room Chair Rail Fantastic Living Room Wainscoting Painting Ideas Have.";i:3;s:51:"Beforeafter decorating is still a work in progress.";i:4;s:99:"Chair rails designs arresting rail to decorating your house new home kitchen wall with metal ideas.";i:5;s:234:"Chair rail moldings installed along the walls first came into use as a buffer to prevent the backs of chairs from hitting delicate plaster walls in dining rooms where chairs were constantly being moved back and forth around the table.";i:6;s:129:"As plaster walls turned into wallboard and formal dining rooms lost their popularity so too did chair rails fade from prominence.";i:7;s:127:"Often molding and chair rails work with more traditional styles and in more tradional rooms often for instance the dining room.";i:8;s:84:"You have a mix of styles for instance the piece in the picture above is more modern.";i:9;s:128:"As well the framing around the windows is more modern and heavier and I think a more delicate chair rail would conflict with it.";i:10;s:167:"In the case of the latter chair rail molding establishes an interiors proportion and scale adding space and elegance to otherwise standard straight-up-and-down spaces.";i:11;s:189:"Available in a number of designs from classic to cutting edge and adaptable to any homes color palette chair rail molding is a seemingly minute detail that makes a night and day difference.";i:12;s:205:"A chair rail also known as a dado rail is a horizontal piece of trim that usually runs the perimeter of a room approx 36 from the floor but can also be awkwardly placed on a single wall popular in the 90s.";i:13;s:137:"When you have a chair rail it can be hard to figure out whether to use the SAME paint colour on the upper and lower portion of the walls.";i:14;s:138:"Historically chair rails were used to protect plaster when chairs were backed up against the walls to clear space in the middle of a room.";i:15;s:79:"Like many functional inventions this one became more decorative over the years.";i:16;s:104:"It became common to use the rail as a divider strip for paint or wallpaper to create a contrasting look.";i:17;s:77:"Oct 28 2015 - Explore Bobbi Jo Thompsons board Chair Rail Ideas on Pinterest.";i:18;s:53:"See more ideas about chair rail home home remodeling.";i:19;s:98:"Build columns add chair rails and hang picture and plate rails for extra details around your home.";i:20;s:111:"How to Install a Sophisticated Chair Rail Transform the look of your wall with a simple yet elegant chair rail.";i:21;s:93:"Chair rail ideas chair rail molding paint ideas chair rail paint ideas best chair rail ideas.";i:22;s:36:"Chair Rails In Kitchen Design Ideas.";i:23;s:71:"Chair Rail Ideas Bathroom About Designs And Colors Bedroom Dining Room.";i:24;s:42:"Paint color is Valspar Martha Cooper rose.";i:25;s:126:"Chair rail moulding is an elegant finish that can add a tasteful touch to any room especially when paired with crown moulding.";i:26;s:75:"However figuring out the right chair rail height can be a challenging task.";i:27;s:127:"If the chair rail is hung at the wrong height it can make a room feel out of proportion and pull the eye in all the wrong ways.";i:28;s:73:"I decided to try a paint sprayer to apply the white below the chair rail.";i:29;s:83:"I figured it would be most successful if I did this before applying the gray above.";i:30;s:91:"This allowed me to avoid taping at all initially except for what I needed over the outlets.";i:31;s:104:"If the white sprayed above the chair rail it wouldnt matter because Id eventually cover it up with gray.";i:32;s:113:"As its name implies the practical purpose of chair rail is to protect walls from damage from the backs of chairs.";i:33;s:101:"However most people who add chair rail to a room do it not for practical purposes but for aesthetics.";i:34;s:131:"Installing chair rail in your home can add an instant touch of class and it also provides you with more opportunities for crafting.";i:35;s:275:"Browse 396 Chair Rail on Houzz Whether you want inspiration for planning chair rail or are building designer chair rail from scratch Houzz has 396 pictures from the best designers decorators and architects in the country including Tatiana Kagan and Lucid Interior Design Inc.";i:36;s:130:"Look through chair rail pictures in different colors and styles and when you find some chair rail that inspires you save it to an.";i:37;s:83:"Chair rail moldings keep the walls from being scuffed by chairs or other furniture.";i:38;s:62:"Additionally chair rail molding has an aesthetic appeal to it.";i:39;s:67:"Believe it or not there is a science to placing chair rail molding.";i:40;s:51:"Many people place the moldings at the wrong height.";i:41;s:82:"Chair rail moulding is often used around the wall of a room parallel to the floor.";i:42;s:90:"It is typically seen installed about one third the distance between the floor and ceiling.";i:43;s:90:"This is where the back of a chair would bump or strike the wall hence the name chair rail.";i:44;s:136:"Ornate profiles can be created by stacking multiple profiles of moulding together such as a chair rail backer and the chair rail itself.";i:45;s:44:"Chair Rail Shop by Pattern Style Chair Rail.";i:46;s:18:"View as Grid List.";i:47;s:49:"Gold Yellow 2X12 Travertine Ogee Chair Rail Line.";i:48;s:18:"Special Price 799.";i:49;s:81:"Locate the studs in the wall and mark them with a pencil or bits of masking tape.";i:50;s:100:"Measure up from the floor andor use a level to mark the chair rail height at each end of each piece.";i:51;s:64:"Have an assistant help hold the chair rail at the marked height.";i:52;s:64:"Basswood Wood CasingChair Rail Moulding The House of Fara 78 in.";i:53;s:28:"X 8 The House of Fara 78 in.";i:54;s:158:"Basswood CasingChair Rail can protect a wall from chairs and furniture or can be used in a variety of other ways to bring a finishing touch to a home project.";i:55;s:73:"Manufactured from solid white hardwood it may be clear coated stained or.";i:56;s:35:"Chair rails with two-colored rooms.";i:57;s:85:"One shade on the top and a different shade on the bottom seem to be the most popular.";i:58;s:241:"This technique works really well in older homes because most of the time these aged homes are already sporting fancy-schmancy architectural details think crown molding and ceiling medallions and this is a fab way to highlight those features.";}}